  <p>
    If you would like your server to be publically monitored by rrd.me.uk, you will
    need to download a copy of the data gathering client script (rrd-client.pl).
    <a href="https://svn.perlgirl.org.uk/dav/RRD-Simple/examples/data_gathering/bin/rrd-client.pl">Click here to download a copy of rrd-client.pl</a>. rrd-client.pl
    currently only works on Linux 2.4 installs or higher, but will soon supoprt
    BSD, Darwin and hopefully more. To get the best results by monitoring as much
    as possible, you should make sure that you have the following programs installed:

    <ul>
      <li>/usr/bin/iostat - Required to monitor hard disk IO</li>
      <li>/usr/bin/vmstat - Required to monitor CPU utilisation</li>
      <li>/usr/bin/sensors - Required to monitor CPU temperature</li>
      <li>/usr/bin/hddtemp - Required to monitor hard disk temperature</li>
    </ul>

    Once you have downloaded rrd-client.pl and tested that it generates output, you
    should add it to your crontab to HTTP POST the data to our server run every 4 or
    5 minutes. A typical crontab entry might be:<br /><br />

    <code>*/5 * * * * sleep 10; /usr/local/bin/rrd-client.pl
       -p http://rrd.me.uk/cgi-bin/rrd-server.cgi >/dev/null 2>&1</code>
  </p>
